review_blob: The dog on the label is also the one who lifted its leg over this can. Awful, awful stuff... would rather drink OE any day of the week.
beer_name: St. Ides High Gravity Malt Liquor

review_blob: There are two kinds of people in this world: those who preferred natty in college... and those who drank beast. Never understood the latter. Only thing worse than this would be beast light ice or king cobra.
There are two kinds of people in this world: those who preferred natty in college... and those who drank beast. Never understood the latter. This is the greatest beer pong beer of all time!

Aroma: Light vanilla
Appearance: Thinner head than I expected, deep, muddy 
Taste: mocha, still searching for the vanilla, BOLD roasted coffee
Palate: mouthy, thick-ish, but not overwhelmingly so
Overall: Very nice, but not quite as good as I expected, given the comments. The roasted coffee flavor dominated this one and I definitely got more of a mocha flavor than vanilla here. Still, a strong dark beer.

If this is on tap, I usually will order it with some kind of salty/hot bar food. It goes amazing with wings, but not so much on its own. Classic English Pub style ale.... dont hate because its common. The head is thick and the liquid is absolutely drinkable. Just wouldnt drink it all the time.... too many other flavors out there!

Aroma: Nothing overwhelming. Sweet, but only a hint of watermelon. 
Appearance: Golden, lighter than a sculpin would appear, if it were a sculpin ;)
Taste: Watermelon bubble gum. Cucumber. Hops. In that order.
Palate: Not as oily as expected. Kind of mouthy yet dissipates quickly.
Overall: Different. Good, yet almost because of the novelty. Dont think I could have too many of these, but interesting to participate in an experiment.
beer_name: Ballast Point Dorado Double IPA - Watermelon

review_blob: 40s and blunts, kid! College made us do strange things... like drink this. Oddly enough, I could probably down one just for nostalgia. No longer the go-to!

Aroma: Peppers. Not the shake kind. Piney hops.
Appearance: orange-gold
Taste: solid. sculpin. heat builds with the hops, leaves, then returns in the throat
Palate: oily ... good
Overall: Hot beer. Good for those who can handle spice. Not sure how you couldnt like hot things.

Aroma: Pineapple. Immediately pineapple. Maybe caramel? Pine. 
Appearance: Amber. Nice, tarnished gold color.
Taste: Smooth. The hops come in waves against the pineapple. Fruity and a little spicy on the finish.
Palate: A little thickness here. Goodness.
Overall: solid offering. Saw my buddy complaining on social media, but hes a snob and plays flute in an Irish band. This is actually good... just takes your palate for a ride b/c of the sweet, sweet waves.

This beer was meant for me. Seriously hopped up Pale Ale that I can session for hours on end. Its my staple and I highly recommend a pint to anyone who hasnt tried it. Aroma: almost a little pine, maybe some citrus. Appearance: Golden. Taste: The bomb. How a Pale Ale should taste. The bar against which all others shall be measured. Palate: not heavy, very smooth. Overall: Duh. Its amazing.

Mango jumps out on the nose, but not so much on the taste. Thats a good thing, in my book, as I dont like overly "fruity" beer. You get a solid dose of the classic IPA hoppy flavor with a mild bit of mango instead. I could drink this all day.
Really enjoyed this one. A bit of pine, a bit of lemon zest, a bit of dill mixed in... really complex and absolutely delicious.

This is probably the best pumpkin brew Ive ever had, except something was different with the 2015 batch. Almost a little acidic or more biting on the tip of your tongue than previous years. Im hoping 2016 goes back to previous performance levels, but lets be honest... this is one amazing brew.
Im dead serious when I say you need to make the trip to Asheville and have this on tap at Wicked Weed. Their sour game is top notch... and this brew explains why. Truly awesome.
beer_name: Wicked Weed Black Angel Cherry Sour

review_blob: Vanilla, vanilla, vanilla! Its like youre trying to play rope-a-dope against a giant vanilla bean beast, but it keeps coming at you. Honestly, its a really nice brew, but you can only take so many punches before youre down for the count. Would advise buying a bottle... but dont expect to session!
beer_name: Double Barley Thrilla in Vanilla Porter

review_blob: Interesting brew. Definitely something youd want on a cold night, but a tad too strong for a real session. Would pair amazingly with some chili or a strong beef stew.
This is one outstanding stout. Had it on nitro at the smokehouse. Really, really nice, chocolatey on the palate and leaves you wanting another pull.
They must have toned down the pepper in the batch Im sipping now. Had a pint with dinner at the smokehouse and had to take home a growler. Really tasty brew here... but I can also handle the heat.
